posts.content: He seems to have some paperwork relating to the chassis number and year. And as for an mot, it doesn't need one as its a 1950, I didn't have to submit one for mine.

pauldee wrote:Does nobody else find this a bit suspicious? Very, very cheap for one of these vehicles & missing log book. Has a dating certificate but you can just send off for these with a chassis number. Previous owner's name and address - could be made up, whois likely to check?

I know the owner. He has had it for a few years.
